						<summary>

						<p>On a stone lying in front of the Kalamēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 12th century.</p>						

						<p>It commences with the Chālukya <hi rend="italic">praśasti;</hi> the name of the king, however, is lost. Barring the mention of Monday and solar eclipse the other details of the date are also lost. It seems to record a gift of money. The inscription is damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
